The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to stable graphs, which are important in game theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory), which is the most likely category. The paper also involves the study of structural properties of fractional matchings, which is a topic in combinatorial optimization, and hence it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The algorithmic results in the paper involve edge- and vertex-removal operations, which are related to graph theory, and hence the paper could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
